<h3><center>
<a href=../newsnight/newsnight.html>NewsNight Minnesota</a> |
<a href=../newtons/index.html>Newton's Apple</a> |
<a href=../alive/index.html>Alive TV</a>  | 
<a href=../almanac/index.html>Almanac</a> | 
<a href=../ktcaprods/archives/index.html>Archives</a> 
* <b>SNEAK PEAKS</b> *
</center></h3><br>
<img  Align=Left src=maps/ktcaprodtitle6.gif height=32 width=498 alt="Sneak Previews"><br clear=all>
<a href=maps/ktcaprodsubtitle6.1.map><img  Align=Left src=maps/ktcaprodsubtitle6.1.gif height=44 width=498 alt="Local Productions" border=0 ISMAP></a><br clear=all><br>
<CENTER><H2>Here are some national programs we have in production.</H2></CENTER>
<hr>
<h2>Liberty!  The American Revolution</h2>

One of the most momentous and important events in history, the birth of the American republic, will be depicted in this series. This major documentary production will combine the sweep of epic history with the personal accounts of both the common and luminous people who shaped this era. At a time when democracy is in resurgence around the world, Liberty! The American Revolution will show how it began in America -- a story filled with drama, courage, surprise, intellectual fervor, and some of the most brilliant people to ever walk this planet.
<p>
Middlemarch Films, of New York, is the co-producer. 


<hr><h2>Pathfinders</h2>

For too many children, basic values like fairness, responsibility and empathy are an abstraction. The aim of Pathfinders, a drama series for 8- to 12-year-olds, is to make values concrete, by placing them in the context of everyday decisions and actions. Pathfinders consists of vivid and exciting half-hour dramas where kids from all walks of life find a range of everyday problems and dilemmas. Without preaching, the series will model the process of thinking through a difficult decision, and show the connection between values and decision-making, between actions and consequences.  
<p>
Lancit Media Productions of New York is the co-producer.


<hr><h2>Donna's Day</h2>

A how-to program that breaks the traditional mold, Donna's Day stars creative parenting specialist Donna Erickson, who shows moms and dads how to have fun with their kids, using simple everyday materials to make projects families can enjoy doing together. 
<p>
In her KTCA series, she offers creative projects designed for a wide range of age levels.


<hr><h2>Photography</h2>

Photography, a three-hour national PBS series to be broadcast in 1997, will explore still photography in America in the twentieth century. Photography will look at the medium in its multiple forms -- recorder of public events, family historian, vehicle of artistic expression, scientific too -- and reveal how it has become such a pervasive presence in twentieth-century life.



<hr><h2>Newton's Apple</h2>

Emmy Award-winning Newton's Apple, the fast-paced and offbeat family science magazine, is now taping segments for its 14th season. Su Chin Pak, Dave Huddleston and Brian Hackney join Peggy Knapp and David Heil to answer viewers' quirky and provocative questions about the science, math and engineering curiosities in all aspects of our lives. Each unique segment is packed with fascinating "ah ha's" for adult viewers and presented with so much fun and energy that younger viewers are hooked as well. Newton's Apple is the most-used broadcast science program in middle schools, and is supported by an on-line service, CD-Roms, interactive videodiscs and a free 35-page Teacher's Guide.


</ul>
<hr>
