<H3>Our studio production facilities include:</H3>
<UL><LI>Total of three studios and two control rooms
<LI>Loading dock to accomodate vehicles as large as an 18-wheeler
<LI>10,000 pound capacity freight elevator, 19' D X 15' H X 12' W, can accomodate large cars and vans
<LI>Green room
<LI>Men's and woman's dressing rooms
<LI>Scene shop to design and build custom sets
</UL>






<H2>STUDIO A:</H2>

<UL><LI>52' x 82', Our Largest Sound Stage
<LI>Two Cycloramas
<LI>Wired For Seven Studio Or Handheld Cameras
<LI>Complete Lighting Grid Suspended 20' High
<UL><LI>Strand Century Lightboard M
<LI>12 - 60 Amp Dimmable Circuits
<li>168 - 20 Amp Dimmable Circuits
</UL>
<LI>GVG 300 Video Switcher
<LI>Neotek Elite 24 x 16 x 2 Audio Console
</UL>
<p>
<H2>STUDIO B:</H2>

<UL><LI>52' x 52' Sound Stage
<LI>One 120' Cyclorama
<LI>Wired For Seven Studio Or Handheld Cameras
<li>Existing Set For Rental
<LI>Complete Lighting Grid Suspended 20' High
<UL><LI>Strand Century Mantrix SX
<LI>6 - 60 Amp Dimmable Circuits
<li>96 - 20 Amp Dimmable Circuits
</UL>
<LI>GVG 300 Video Switcher
<LI>Neotek Elite 24 x 16 x 2 Audio Console
</UL>



<H2>STUDIO C:</H2>

<UL><LI>19' x 27'
<LI>Comfortable Seating For Up To 40 People
<br>Ideal For Satellite Downlink Viewing
<LI>Wired for Two Cameras
<LI>Carpeted Floor
</UL>

<H3>Common Equipment:</H3>
<CENTER><H4>- Video Support -</H4></CENTER>
GVG DPM-700 digital effects, Still store, Halo graphics generator, Computer prompter, etc.
<CENTER><H4>- Cameras -</H4></CENTER>
Ikegami HL-322, HL-43, and others
<CENTER><H4>- Video Tape -</H4></CENTER>
Digital Beta, 1" type C, Betacam SP<br>
3/4" U-Matic, Hi-8, VHS and SVHS also supported
<CENTER><H4>- Audio Support -</H4></CENTER>
Analog 2 tk, 8 tk, 24 tk tape recorders<BR>
Digital 8 tk tape recorders<BR>
See our <A HREF=editing.html>Post Production equipment list</A> for additional facilities

<H3>Studio Sound Isolation:</H3>
<UL><LI>Each studio is a "Box Within A Box" design, with concrete walls 8" thick.
<LI>Studio floors are 4" thick resting on large newprene pads, a technique designed to isolate the studios from an urban environment.
<LI>All mechanical systems also rest on neoprene pads and are located away from the studios to prevent vibrations.
<LI>32 specially constructed sound-isolation doors in the KTCA-TV studio area.
<LI>Studio A and B main doors 11' 8" x 19' 10", weigh 10,000 pounds per pair.
</UL>
