<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Beast of Bardia</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000c42" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00"ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><P><H1>The Beast of Bardia</H1><P><IMG SRC="beastie.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0"><H3>A mammoth lurking in the jungles of Nepal? The reports soundedfabulous, but thecreature was quite real enough to those who had come across it.<P>These pages contain an <A HREF="bardia.html">edited transcript</A> of theChannel 4 programme(transmission: 21 July 1996) that followed an expedition to find out thetruth aboutthe 'Beast of Bardia'. They also include <A HREF="bardia.html#013">background</A> information,suggestions for<A HREF="bardia.html#014">further reading</A> and <A HREF="bardia.html#015">links</A> to related Web sites.</H3><BR CLEAR=LEFT><I>Online 19 July</I><P></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
