<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Mind Field</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><DD><DL><DD><DL><P><IMG SRC="-head.gif" ALIGN=right><H1>THE MIND FIELD</H1><P><B>The way our minds work can often surprise us and, at times, can be totally incomprehensible. These pages look at six aspects of brain behaviour and tries to make sense of our unconscious thoughts and actions.</B> <P><H3><A HREF="-intro.html">Introduction</A></H3><P><H3><A HREF="-lying.html">Lying</A>: the lying game</H3><P><B>How telling untruths keeps the world going round; why some children lie to be loved; what makes a compulsive liar.</B> <P><H3><A HREF="-power.html">Power</A>: Power struggles</H3><P><B>Power through persuasion; why we give power to others - and why some people seek it; 'soft' power qualities.</B> <P><H3><A HREF="-memory.html">Memory</A>: Memories</H3><P><B>How we remember; what can be done to improve memory; how age alters memory.</B> <P><H3><A HREF="-risk.html">Risk-taking and Gambling</A>: The gambling instinct</H3><P><B>How some people seek and others try to reduce risks; the physical effects of taking risks; gambling as an addiction.</B> <P><H3><A HREF="-percep.html">Perception</A>: Seeing things</H3><P><B>How different points of view are created; how optimism and depression colour the way we perceive the world; how we learn to distinguish between reality and fantasy.</B> <P><H3><A HREF="-fear.html">Fear</A>: Feeling afraid</H3><P><B>How we abhor yet seek fear; what its function is; how we learn to fear and to handle fear; how phobias develop.</B> <P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"><P><FONT SIZE=1>Photo: GJLP-CNRI/Science Photo Library)</FONT></DD></DL></DD></DL></BODY></HTML>
