<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Trial and Error</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000c42" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><P><IMG SRC="trial.gif" ALIGN=top BORDER=1 ALT="Trial and Error"><P><H3>On 26 June 1996 Channel 4's <I>TRIAL AND ERROR</I> investigated the conviction for murder of Eddie Gilfoyle. In 1992 his eight and a half months pregnant wife Paula was found hanging in the garage of their home. This is an <A HREF="gilfoyle.html">edited transcript</A> of the programme which revealed new evidence demonstrating Gilfoyle's innocence.</H3><I>Online 27 June</I><P><H3>On 27 June 1996 Channel 4's <I>TRIAL AND ERROR</I> looked at the conviction of Jamil Chowdhary for a brutal murder carried out during a raid on a petrol station on 1 February 1991. This is an <A HREF="chowdhary.html">edited transcript</A> of the programme which raised serious questions about the evidence used to convict Chowdhary - and used the latest technology to demonstrate he could not have been the killer.</H3><I>Online 28 June</I><P></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
