<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Get serious!</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000c42" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1>	<TR>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=225><IMG SRC="thinker.gif" ALIGN=TOP></TD>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=225><H2>This is the index of serious programme support on-line. Some of these modules also 		exist in print. Others - like <I>Travelog</I> and <I>Africa Express</I> - have been specially 		developed for the web site. We're constantly adding to this section to build up a 		useful archive on the web. So whether or not you saw the programmes, check out 		these pages for a mind-expanding experience.</H2></TD>	</TR></TABLE><DL><DD><DL><DD><DL><DD><P><A HREF="getnetted/getnett1.html"><H2>Get Netted!</H2><img src="_gifs/getnet.gif" ALT="Get Netted!" ALIGN=LEFT></A>As a project to accompany the <I>Get Netted</I> series, Channel 4 provided various groups who would not otherwise have access with the means to explore the Internet. Here the groups give an account of their experiences - positive,negative and downright infuriating - as they ventured into cyberspace for the first time.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></DL></DD><P><A HREF="xpress/xphome.html"><H2>Africa Express '96</H2><P><img src="_gifs/xpress.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A><I>Africa Express</I> uses Africa-based correspondents to seek outthe real stories behind the superficial coverage of the continent in thenews. These pages provide backgroundinformation and links on each report, and resources for those wishing to find outmore about Africa in general.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><DL><DD><P><A HREF="travelog96/travelog.html"><H2>Travelog '96</H2><P><img src="_gifs/travelog.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A><I>Travelog</I> reveals the essential character of a wide variety of destinations. An invaluable first stop on your travels, this big byte provides information on all the places visited in the series. It has links to travel guides to the destinations, along with links to general travel resources on web.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></DL></DD><P><A HREF="equinox95/equinox95_Q&A.html"><H2>Equinox 1995</H2><P></A>Questions and answers from the 1995 run of the science and technology series.<DL><DD><P><A HREF="hiddenhands/hhand.html"><H2>Hidden Hands: A different history of modernism</H2><P><img src="_gifs/hhand.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>Examines the various and often unspoken influences on the history of modernism. Originally shown in October 1995. A <A HREF="../paperbkup/bamhidd.html">booklet</A> is also available.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></DL></DD><P><A HREF="cybersecrecy/cyber000.html"><H2>Equinox: Cybersecrecy</H2><P></A>First shown in September 1995, this programme examines the strange science of cryptography, or code-making, which is at the centre of a fierce battle between governments, scientists and civil libertarians. <BR CLEAR=LEFT><DL><DD><P><A HREF="firstsex95/fsintro.html"><H2>First Sex 95</H2><P><img src="_gifs/fs95.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>This series - on airduring June and July 1995 - is the only peaktime series on Britishtelevision presenting stories with a particular significance for women,from a feminist perspective. We have selected some of the morecontroversial topics raised in the series and focused on those subjectsthat illustrate some key cultural changes confronting women today.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></DL></DD><P><A HREF="mindfield/-mind.html"><H2>The Mind Field</H2><P><img src="_gifs/mind.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>The way our minds work can often surprise us and, at times can betotally incomprehensible. These pages try to make sense of ourunconscious thoughts and actions.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><DL><DD><P><a HREF="potnight/potnight.html"><H2>Pot Night</H2><P><img src="_gifs/potnight.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>Channel 4 devoted a whole night's programming to the subject ofcannabis. These pages contain material adapted and abridged from theChannel 4 booklet published to accompany the programmes.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></DL></DD><P><a HREF="rave/rave.html"><H2>Equinox: Rave New World</H2><P><img src="_gifs/rave.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>Pop culture has met the microchip and a strange new creature has emerged.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
