<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Travelog 1996 - Whitstable - The gen</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><BASEFONT SIZE=4><A NAME="TOP"><P><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1>	<TR>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=76><A HREF="../travelog.html"><IMG SRC="../smtrav.gif" ALT="Travelog home page" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=76 BORDER=1"></A></TD>		<TD VALIGN TOP><P><FONT SIZE=6>Whitstable - the gen</FONT></TD>			</TR></TABLE><DL><DD><DL><DD>		<FONT SIZE=4>		<A HREF="#001">Introduction</A>		<BR><A HREF="#002">Tourist information</A>		<BR><A HREF="#003">Links</A>						<P><A HREF="whitst1.html">return to Whitstable page</A></FONT>		</DL></DD></DL></DD><P><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1>	<TR>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=76><IMG SRC="whitmap1.gif" WIDTH=76 ALT="Inset map" ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0></TD>		<TD VALIGN TOP><IMG SRC="whitmap2.gif" WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=298 ALT="Main Map" ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0></TD>	</TR></TABLE><DL><DD><DL><DD><P><A NAME="001"><H2><B>Introduction</B></H2><P>Whitstable is a quiet seaside town on the north coast of Kent, whose long pebbly beach and rows of faded wooden beach-huts and clapboard houses have remained largely undiscovered by tourists. It is home to a close-knit community, and residents are concerned to keep the place pretty much as it is - great care is taken to ensure that any new buildings are in keeping with their surroundings.<P><IMG SRC="whitspic3.gif" BORDER=1><P>However, despite its sedate charm, Whitstable has associations of horror. It was once a major smuggling port, and the names of its narrow alleys - Squeezegut, for example - tell their own tale. It was also home for 35 years to Hammer star Peter Cushing (see links).<P><IMG SRC="whitspic2.gif" BORDER=1><P>Steve Blacknell visited his childhood haunt for <I>Travelog</I>, taking in on the way Seasalter, whose peace is undisturbed in summer or winter. Once in Whitstable the first stop was Seasalter Shellfish (see below), who farm the oysters that are its most famous export. Shellfish are big business in Whitstable, and there are a number of excellent fish restaurants. One of the best is next-door to the beautifully restored cinema.<P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A><P><A NAME="002"><H2><B>Tourist information</B></H2><P>Whitstable can be reached by rail or car. There's plenty of good bed-and-breakfast accommodation and a couple of hotels. One or two of the pubs also offer rooms. For further information contact:<P><B>Whitstable Tourist Office</B> <BR>7 Oxford Street<BR>Whitstable<BR>01227 275482 <BR><P>The South East England Tourist Board Web site has details of the<BR><A HREF="http://www.se-eng-tourist-board.org.uk/seetb/attract/oyster.htm">Oyster Fishery Exhibition</A>. Or contact:<BR><B>Seasalter Shellfish (Whitstable) Limited</B> <BR>End of East Quay<BR>Whitstable Harbour<BR>Kent CT5 1AB<BR>Tel: 01227 272003<BR><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A><P><A NAME="003"><H2><B>Links</B></H2><P><A HREF="http://kentnet.co.uk/kentinfo.htm">Kent Guide</A>: places to visit, hotels, shopping, leisure, what's on where.<P><A HREF="http://www.se-eng-tourist-board.org.uk/seetb/">South East England Tourist Board Home Page</A> <P><A HREF="http://alethea.ukc.ac.uk/WhatsOn/WhitCinema">What's on: Whitstable Cinema</A><P>Restaurant guide: <A HREF="http://www.internetweb.co.uk/WEBPAGES/rest/re746.htm">Whitstable Oyster Fisher Co</A> <P><A HREF="http://www.wh.whoi.edu/homepage/faq.html"><IMG SRC="bilcrabicon.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=1">Fish? FAQ:</A>   includes some useful facts about oysters.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://www.veg.org/veg/People/cushing.html">Peter Cushing OBE - an obituary</A><P><A HREF="http://www.iglou.com/why/fish.htm"><IMG SRC="fish.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=1">The World of Creative Cookery: Fish and Seafood Courses:</A>  some interesting recipes for anyone inspired to try their hand at preparing fish and seafood themselves.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
