<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Travelog 1996 - Postcard from Whitstable</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><BASEFONT SIZE=4><A NAME="TOP"><P><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1>	<TR>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=76><A HREF="../travelog.html"><IMG SRC="../smtrav.gif" ALT="Travelog home page" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=76 BORDER=1"></A></TD>		<TD VALIGN TOP><P><FONT SIZE=6>Postcard from Whitstable</FONT>	</TR></TABLE>		<DL><DD><DL><DD> <FONT SIZE=4><P><A HREF="whitst1.html">return to Whitstable page</A></FONT><P><IMG SRC="whitspc1.gif" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=361 BORDER=0><P><FONT SIZE=5><B><P>Whitstable is a place where the sublime and the ridiculous peacefully co-exist - 'peacefully' being the operative word. The pace of life is so slow here that time sometimes seems to have stopped altogether, somewhere around the 1950s perhaps. And that's how the locals plan to keep it, though developers have other ideas.<P>It's only in the famous harbour that there's a hint of hustle - even on a Wednesday afternoon, when everything else is closed. Shellfish are big business here - the oyster has always been Whitstable's world.</B></FONT><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
