.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="gopher://ra.cs.ohiou.edu/11/dept.servers/aern/">African EducationResearch Network:</A> brings together educators from African and NorthAmerican universities to share reports of research studies and to considerdevelopmental issues.<P><A HREF="http://www.sas.upenn.edu/African_Studies/Home_Page/AS.html">African Studies (University of Pennsylvania) home page:</A> bulletin board; Africaguide; direct feeds from Africa; country-specific pages for Africa;black/African Internet resources; multimedia archives; what's new on theAfrican Studies Web site.<P><A HREF="http://www.odci.gov/cia/publications/95fact/">CIA World Factbook:</A> maps, geography, people, government, etc.<P><A HREF="http://www.city.net/regions/africa/"><IMG SRC="city_net_title.gif" BORDER=0">City.Net - Africa:</A> combines the features of an atlas, gazetteer, almanac,guide book and newspaper. Aims to show different perspectives on each community.<P><A HREF="http://town.hall.org/Archives/radio/IMS/CommonGround/950801_comm_00_ITH.html">Common Ground - African Problems, African Solutions:</A> the head of the African Capacity Building Foundation outlines some current African solutions to African problems (audio files).<P><A HREF="http://www.web.apc.org/~econews/ena4-18.html">EcoAfrica News:</A> an NGO initiative that analyses global environment and development issues from an African perspective and reports on local, national, and regional activities that contribute to global solutions. <P><A HREF="http://www.cs.indiana.edu/hyplan/dmulholl/exodus.html"><IMG SRC="afr_flag3.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Exodus:</A> guide to flags; national pages; good pan-African links.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://206.74.57.36/geography/africa/PAGE00.HTM"><IMG SRC="grph01.jpg" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Gold Stag International Airport - Africa:</A> country profiles.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://www.afroam.org/africa/"><IMG SRC="infoonafrica.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Info on Africa:</A> links and resources.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://the.arc.co.uk/arm/popAfrica.html"><IMG SRC="arm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Map of population density in Africa</A><BR CLEAR=LEFT><P> <A HREF="http://www.oneworld.org/index.html">One World Online:</A> includesnews from over 80 countries; also global themes - economy, biodiversity,women's rights, Internet, etc. Plus links to the home pages of 60-pluspartner organisations.<P><A HREF="http://www.nando.net/ans/pana/FEED/PANAFEED.html"><IMG SRC="panabar1.gif" BORDER=0">Panafrican News Agency:</A> news stories; environment; economics; science andhealth; sports; Africa press review. Updated throughout the day.<P><A HREF="http://www.nosc.mil/planet_earth/info_modern.html#pehptext08">Planet Earth - World Region 2:</A> clickable image map; World Book; Yahoolinks.<P><A HREF="http://www.soas.ac.uk/">School of Oriental and AfricanStudies:</A> courses; diary; library; research and publications. See also'Book, journal and music suppliers' below.<A HREF="http://www.gatech.edu/bgsa/blackpages/history.html">Universal Black Pages:</A> the diaspora; businesses; history; resources; art; spoken word; life; written word; music; professional organisations; entertainment; educational opportunities/activities; engineering, science, and technology.<P><A HREF="http://www.w3.org/hypertext/DataSources/WWW/Africa.html"><IMG SRC="listserve.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Virtual Tourist - Africa:</A> a geographic directory of all the Web serversin the world.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><A HREF="http://www-fes.gmd.de/help/">Women in East Africa:</A> (brief) introduction and articles about women in Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania.<P><A HREF="http://neal.ctstateu.edu/history/world_history/archives/archive31.html">World History Archives - Africa:</A> documents on economics and foreignaid; society and labour; politics; culture and consciousness.<P><A HREF="http://www.aztec.co.za/biz/africa/"><IMG SRC="alchemy.gif" ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0"><P>World Wide Marketeer's Alchemy of Africa:</A> includes information and links to information on African culture, natural history, religion and business. Plus Africa's top ten; Live Chat.<P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A><P><A NAME=002><H2><B>Culture</B></H2><P><A HREF="http://www.lib.virginia.edu/dic/exhib/93.ray.aa/African.html"><IMG SRC="title.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">African Art - Aesthetics and Meaning:</A> Bayly Art Museum (University ofVirginia) exhibition catalogue.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://www.uni-mainz.de/~bender/AMA-files/ama_index.html">AfricanMusic Resources Online:</A> part of the African Music Archive of theInstitute of Ethnology and African Studies at Johannes-Gutenberg-University,Mainz.<P><A HREF="http://www.sas.upenn.edu/African_Studies/Home_Page/WWW_Links.html#Arts">African Studies (University of Pennsylvania) art sites links</A><P><A HREF="http://www.sas.upenn.edu/African_Studies/Home_Page/mcgee.html#Black/African%20&%20Cultural%20Issues">African Studies (University of Pennsylvania) culture links</A><P><A HREF="http://www-sul.stanford.edu/depts/ssrg/africa/afrlit.html">African and Afro-Caribbean Literature Reference Works:</A> bibliography.<P><A HREF="http://www.ina.fr/Music/Pays/index.en.html">Afro-Caribbean music:</A> geographic index to artists and albums<P><A HREF="http://artswire.org/Artswire/www/caribctr/home.html"><IMG SRC="ccclogo8.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Caribbean Cultural Center - African Diaspora Institute (US):</A>traditional music,song and dance; philosophy of Africa-based religions; international shop.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ai.mit.edu/~isbell/HFh/black/bhcal-toc.html">Deeper Shade:</A> black history, literature and film reviews<P><A HREF="http://www.sil.org/ethnologue/countries/index.html#Africa">Ethnologue by Country:</A> information on the different languages spoken ineach country and which groups speak them.<P><A HREF="http://matisse.net/%7Ejplanet/afmx/ahome.htm#Z"><IMG SRC="6drmr.jpg" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Music of Africa and the African Diaspora:</A> links to details of artists by country and artist name. Plus related African links and African music sources<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="gopher://chop.isca.uiowa.edu:8337/11/.uiowa/.art/.stanley/dir.info">Stanley Collection of African Art (University of Iowa)</A><P><AHREF="http://nz.com/webnz/creative-cgi/special/trance/trance.htm">TranceAfrica:</A> 'The magical Trance African experience will transportwilling adventurers to the deepest, unexplored rhythms.' This site also looks atthe science of the music.<IMG SRC="trance2.gif" BORDER=0"><P><A HREF="news:soc.culture.african">Usenet African culture newsgroup</A><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A><P><A NAME=003><H2><B>Travel</B></H2><P><A HREF="http://www.africa.com/~venture/afralt/aboutaa.htm">African Alternatives:</A> information and booking services for nature andadventure travellers in Southern Africa.<P><A HREF="http://www.gorp.com/atb/africa.htm"><IMG SRC="bookstore.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Africa Books & Maps:</A> the Adventurous Traveler Bookstore's database of travel books and maps on Africa.<P><A HREF="http://www.kilimanjaro.com/"><IMG SRC="kilimanj.jpg" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Kilimanjaro Adventure Travel:</A> African travel information.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://roughguides.com/RG_WWW/rgtrav.html"><IMG SRC="global.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Rough Guide to Travel:</A> catalogue includes books on West Africa, Zimbabweand Botswana.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://www.cdc.gov/travel/regions.htm">Traveler's Health Information:</A> US government advice; index to all African countries.<P><A HREF="http://www.checkin.com/database/tourism.html"><IMG SRC="untouroff.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0">Worldwide tourism offices administered by UN</A><BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A><P><A NAME=004><H2><B>Book, journal and music suppliers</B></H2><P><B>The Africa Book Centre</B><BR>38 King Street<BR>London WC2E 8JT<BR>Tel: (0171) 240 6649<BR>Fax: (0171) 479 0309<BR><I>Britain's leading specialist supplier of African books.</I><P><B>School of Oriental and African Studies (SOAS)</B><BR>Thornhaugh Street<BR>Russell Square<BR>London WC1H 0XG<BR>Tel: 0171 637 2388<BR>Fax: 0171 636 3634<BR><I>SOAS facilitates the publication of books and journals in its fields ofstudy.Lists are available from the Publications Officer; books may be seen in andpurchased from 24 Russell Square (top floor).</I><P><B>Stern's Africa Record Centre</B><BR>293 Euston Road<BR>London NW1 3AD<BR>Tel: 0171 387 5550<BR><I>Has an excellent selection of African contemporary music.</I><P><B>Carnaq Distribution and Imports</B> <BR>51 Grovelands Road<BR>Palmers Green<BR>London N13 4RJTel: 0181 882 5102<BR>Fax: 0181 372 0143<BR><I>Specialist in African music and salsa. Send SAE or phone for moreinformation.</I><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
