<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Africa Express: Fashion Notes - factfile</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><BASEFONT SIZE=4><A NAME="TOP"><DL><DD><DL><DD><P><P><FONT SIZE=6>Fashion Notes - factfile</FONT></BODY></HTML><P><FONT SIZE=4><UL><LI><P><I>La Sape</I> is an acronym for La Soci&eacutet&eacute des Ambienceurs et des 	Personnes d'Elegance<P>	<LI><P>Sapeurs are almost all men - Zairean women do go to soukous concerts dressed to 	kill, but they tend to wear Zairean clothes<P>	<LI><P>Sapeurs' favourite designers are Gianni Versace and Jean-Paul Gaultier. A Versace 	shirt costs between 500 and 900<P>	<LI><P>It costs the equivalent of 1 to get into a concert by a top Zairean band such as 	Zaiko Langa Langa<P>	<LI><P>1 is approximately the equivalent of the average weekly wage in Zaire<P>	<LI><P>Sapeur culture has spread from Kinshasa to immigrant communities in Brussels, 	Paris, Geneva and London - where there are about 100,000 Zaireans</UL></B></FONT><P><A HREF="#TOP"><IMG SRC="../../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0></A><TR>			<P><TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=88><A HREF="xpsapt2.html"><IMG SRC="../xpback.gif" ALT="Background" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=88 HEIGHT=50 BORDER=0></A></TD>		<P><TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=88><A HREF="../xphome.html"><IMG SRC="../xphome.gif" ALT="Africa Express Home Page" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=88 HEIGHT=50 BORDER=0></A></TD>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=88><A HREF="../xplinks/xplinks.html"><IMG SRC="../xplink.gif" ALT="Africa Links" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH=88 HEIGHT=50 BORDER=0></A></TD>		<TD VALIGN TOP WIDTH=88><A HREF="../xpconn.html"><IMG SRC="../xpconn.gif" A