<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>get netted</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00"ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H1><FONT COLOR="#00FF00">get netted</H1><H2>first steps in cyberspace</H2></FONT><B><P>As a project to accompany the <I>Get Netted</I> series, Channel 4 decided toprovide various groups who would not otherwise have access with the meansto explore the Internet. The purpose was to see what uses, if any, theycould find for it.<P>Here the groups give an account of their experiences - positive,negative and downright infuriating - as they ventured into cyberspace forthe first time.Their stories reveal both the strengths and the weaknesses of the Internetas it is now, suggesting ways in which it must change if it is really tocarry us all into a new age of information.<P><I>These pages are also available in printed form. The <A HREF="../paperbkup/bscgetn.html">booklet</A> includesa practical guide to getting started on the Internet.</I><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"><P><IMG SRC="mlinks.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=83><A HREF="http://www.gn.apc.org/hive/">Hive</A><FONT COLOR="#FF9940"> isa newWeb site which the ScarmanTrust has developed to build on the <I>Get Netted</I> project. It is intended tobe a virtual clearing house for the voluntary/community sector, where youcan trade your skills and buy what you want in return, generate newresources, make new contacts and build new alliances, and share yourexperiences and views with a global audience.</FONT><BR CLEAR=LEFT><B><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"><UL>	<LI><A HREF="getnett2.html">Introduction</A><P>	<A HREF="getnett3.html"><LI>New lamps for old:<UL>	<LI>Welfare State International</A></UL><P>	<LI><A HREF="getnett4.html">The learning ark:<UL>		<LI>Park School</A></UL><P>	<LI><A HREF="getnett5.html">Get Letted:<UL>		<LI>Letslink UK</A></UL><P>	<LI><A HREF="getnett6.html">The surfing community:<UL>		<LI>The Cedar Centre</A></UL><P>	<LI><A HREF="getnett7.html">Small world:<UL>		<LI>Charles Wooton College</A></UL><P>	<LI><A HREF="getnett8.html">Virtual accommodation:<UL>		<LI>Surface</A></UL><P>	<LI><A HREF="getnett9.html">Internet access points</A></UL><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"><FONT SIZE=2><P>Project co-ordinator: Matthew Pike<BR>Editor: Paula Snyder<BR>Consultant editor: Peter Millson<BR>Additional material written by Matthew Pike<BR></FONT><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
