<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Travelog 1997 - Traveller's Links</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#E7C46C" VLINK="#BA7335"><BASEFONT SIZE=3><A NAME="TOP"><DL><DD><DL><DD><P><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=12><TR><TD VALIGN TOP><IMG SRC="../graphics/4logo.gif" BORDER=0></TD><TD VALIGN TOP><A HREF="../itinerary.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/itin97.gif" ALT="97 itinerary" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD VALIGN TOP><A HREF="../travelog97.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/smtrav97.gif" ALT="Programme information" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD VALIGN TOP><A HREF="../../travelog96/travelog.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/smtrav96.gif" ALT="General information" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE>		<P><H1>Traveller's links</H1><FONT SIZE=4><P><B>Travellers are well served on the Web. Here are a few starting points for making your travel plans.</B></FONT> <P><A HREF="http://www.timeout.co.uk/">Time Out Net:</A> city guides and arts and entertainment listings for Amsterdam, Berlin, London, Madrid, New York, Paris, Prague, Rome and San Francisco, plus on-the-spot reports, features and a free classified advertising service. Listings are updated weekly on Wednesdays. <P><A HREF="http://www.lonelyplanet.com.au/lp.htm"><IMG SRC="lplogo3.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0>Lonely Planet travel guides:</A> Down-to-earth travel information designed to kickstart your travels and help you along the way.<BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="http://www.roughguides.com/">Rough Guides to Travel:</A> contemporary, practical guides for independent travel. From the home page you can browse the titles, read introductionsto the countries, and check on further reading. <P><A HREF="http://www.city.net/cnx/about_cnx.html"><IMG SRC="city_net.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0><P>City.Net:</A> a new kind of guide that combines the features of an atlas, gazetteer, almanac, guide book and newspaper. Aims to show different perspectives on each community. <P><A HREF="http://wings.buffalo.edu/world/">Virtual Tourist:</A> a geographic directory of WWW servers worldwide. Tour the virtual world and send in your comments. Note: this service does not contain information for tourists.<P><A HREF="http://wings.buffalo.edu/world/vt2/">Virtual Tourist 2:</A> a map-based interface to City.Net, the Web's most extensive library of community (see above).   <P><A HREF="http://www.rednet.co.uk/travelmag/"><IMG SRC="tmglink1.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0>Travelmag</A>  includes: regular items on health, world news, trade news, good deals and travel books; features from around the globe; and Webwide links for independent travellers. <BR CLEAR=LEFT> <P><A HREF="http://www.hols.com/">The Internet Holiday Centre:</A> flights, holidays, hotels, car hire, brochures. Frequently updated.<P><A HREF="http://www.yell.co.uk/yell/newweb/travel/index.html">Yellow Pages Travel:</A> comprehensive guide to travel and holiday services.<P><A HREF="http://www.travlang.com/"><IMG SRC="travlangworld.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0>Travlang</A> provides a variety of useful tools for the traveller andthose interested in learning a foreign language. <BR CLEAR=LEFT>  <P><A HREF="http://www.ora.com/gnn/bus/ora/oratt/index.html"><IMG SRC="tt-nav.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALIGN=TOP BORDER=0>Travelers' Tales Books</A> catalogue and sample essays.  <BR CLEAR=LEFT><P><A HREF="news:rec.travel">rec.travel</A>: newsgroup for travel in general.<P><HR WIDTH=80%></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
