<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>RISK-TAKING AND GAMBLING</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H2><A HREF="-mind.html">The Mind Field:</A> <A HREF="-risk.html"> Risk-taking and Gambling</A></H2><STRONG>Spreadbetting</STRONG> is a means of taking risks on the basis that the more right you are, the more you win - e.g. you guess that a horse race will be won by 30 seconds, and not by only 5, as predicted by the bookmaker. Clients place bets if they think they can assess the outcome more accurately than the published odds. Financial futures markets operate in a similar way.<P><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
