<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>RISK-TAKING AND GAMBLING</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H2><A HREF="-mind.html">The Mind Field:</A> <A HREF="-risk.html"> Risk-taking and Gambling</A></H2><H2>Are you a gambling addict?</H2>1  Do you spend time reliving gambling experiences, and/or thinking of ways to get money with which to gamble?<P>2  Do you spend more on gambling now than you did a year ago?<P>3  Have you tried to gamble less or stop altogether - and failed?<P>4  Are you restless or irritable when you don't gamble?<P>5  Does gambling make you feel better when you're anxious, fed up or cross?<P>6  After losing money gambling, do you gamble more the following day to try to get your money back? (This is called 'chasing losses'.)<P>7  Do you lie to family or others about how much you gamble?<P>8  Have you stolen, forged another's signature or taken money from the household bills to finance gambling?<P>9  Have you lost a job, an important friendship and/or an educational or career opportunity because of gambling?<P>10  Do you rely on others to provide money to relieve a desperate financial situation caused by gambling?<P><H4>If you have answered 'yes' to at least five of these questions, you may have a <A HREF="risk15.html" NAME="">gambling problem</A>.</H4><P><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
