<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>PERCEPTION</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H2><A HREF="-mind.html">The Mind Field:</A> <A HREF="-percep.html"> Perception</A></H2><H3>Perception <A HREF="percep9.html" NAME="">problems</A></H3>People who see the world very differently to the rest of us are those with psychotic disorders, neurological disorders or brain disease. <P><STRONG>Psychotic disorders:</STRONG> <A HREF="http://www.ucar.edu/pendulum"><KBD>Manic depression</KBD></A> and schizophrenia are the most common.<P><STRONG>Neurological disorders:</STRONG><br><UL><LI>Migraine: pain, alterations in visual perception.<P><LI>Synaesthesia: the senses are 'cross-wired' and get mixed up, with an effect similar to that of taking LSD; colours may be heard, or smells tasted.<P></UL><STRONG>Brain diseases:</STRONG> Alzheimer's disease, Parkinson's disease and motor neurone disease, among others.<P><KBD><A HREF="http://avocado.pc.helsinki.fi/~janne/mood/mood.html">Mood disorders</A></KBD><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
