<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>FEAR</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H2><A HREF="-mind.html">The Mind Field:</A> <A HREF="-fear.html"> Fear</A></H2><STRONG><A HREF="http://www.actwin.com/NLP/"><KBD>Neuro-linguistic programming</KBD></A></STRONG> (NLP) is based on many other therapies, especially Gestalt, family and brief therapies. NLP therapists treat phobias by having the person recall the bad experience associated with the phobia and rewrite the event in his or her imagination. The rewritten version will more closely match most people's idea of reality - e.g. frogs aren't harmful, open spaces are OK, etc.<P><EM>For a local NLP therapist,</EM> contact: Sue Gazey, ANLP Administration Office, 48 Corser Street, Old Swinford, Stourbridge, West Midlands DY8 2DQ, tel: (01384) 443935.<P><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
