<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>FEAR</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H2><A HREF="-mind.html">The Mind Field:</A> <A HREF="-fear.html"> Fear</A></H2><H3>Avoiding the effects of fear</H3>Meditation, yoga and exercise all help keep you fit and relaxed in the long term and less prone to the physiological wear and tear that stresses and fears bring in ordinary life. However, once fear starts to rule your body and your mind, it's time to seek professional help. <EM>To find a local counsellor</EM>, contact: British Association for Counselling, 37a Sheep Street, Rugby, Warwickshire CV21 3BX, tel: (01788) 78328/9.<P><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
