&amp; Charles, 1990.<P><I><B>A Spy's London: A walk book of 136 sites in Central London relating to spies,spycatchers, &amp; subversives from more than a century of London's secrethistory</B></I> by Roy Berkeley, Leo Cooper Ltd, 1994.<P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"><P><H3><A NAME="finding">Finding out more on the Internet</A></H3><P><A HREF="http://rschp2.anu.edu.au:8080/cipher.html">Classic ciphers and their weaknesses</A><P><A HREF="http://rschp2.anu.edu.au:8080/crypt.html">Cryptography and PGP page</A><P><A HREF="http://draco.centerline.com:8080/~franl/crypto.html">Cryptography, PGP and your privacy</A><P><A HREF="ftp://scotch.csua.berkeley.edu/pub/cypherpunks/Home.html">Cypherpunks home page</A><P><A HREF="http://www.brute.cl.cam.ac.uk/brute/">Cypherpunks key-cracking ring</A><P><A HREF="http://rschp2.anu.edu.au:8080/howpgp.html">How PGP and RSA works</A><P><A HREF="http://rschp2.anu.edu.au:8080/pgpfaq.html">PGP FAQ</A><P><A HREF="http://euclid.math.fsu.edu/Science/math.html">Mathematics at the WWW Virtual Library</A><P><A HREF="http://www.itr.ch/~pheinzma/crypt.html">Cryptography pointers</A><P><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/">Electronic Frontier Foundation</A><P><B><I>Relevant e-mail addresses</I></B><P><A HREF="mailto:mab@research.att.com">Matt Blaze</A><P><A HREF="mailto:prz@acm.org">Phil Zimmermann</A><P><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
