<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>FIRST SEX</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#000000" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#00FFFF" VLINK="#FFFF00" ALINK="#FF00FF"><TABLE><TR><TD><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG SRC="/_gifs/4wobcircle.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD><TD><IMG SRC="/_gifs/wobcircle1.gif" ALIGN=left BORDER=0></TD></TR></TABLE><P><P><DL><DD><DL><DD><H2><A HREF="fsintro.html">First Sex</A></H2><H1>It's my life</H1>In a society dominated by media images of beautiful people, sexual fulfilment appears to be the preserve of fast talking, fast living svelte young beings. Whilst most accept that such supposed perfection is not necessarily a passport to a multi orgasmic existence, we are instilled from a very young age with the expectation, for good or ill, that we will mature to encounter sex and romantic love. <P><STRONG>The following pages provide:</STRONG><UL><LI>an <A HREF="fslif2.html" NAME="">introduction</A> to problems faced by women with learning disabilities in relation to their sexuality<P><LI><A HREF="fslif3.html" NAME="">education is for everyone</A> - the need for sex education for all children regardless of disability<P><LI><A HREF="fslif4.html" NAME="">Who controls fertility?</A><P><LI><A HREF="fslif5.html" NAME="">Permitted relationships</A> - how access problems and other people's attitudes, can restrict relationships<P><LI>Where you can go for<A HREF="fslif6.html" NAME=""> support, advice and information</A></UL><P><IMG SRC="../../_gifs/_line1.gif" WIDTH=448 HEIGHT=8 BORDER=0"></DL></DD></DL></DD></BODY></HTML>
