<head>
<title>Z Magazine: A Political Monthly</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#EEFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h2 align=center><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/lgzmag.gif" alt="Z Magazine: A Political Monthly" align=bottom border=0 width=462 height=160></a></h2>
<hr>
<p align=center><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37></a><a href="whatsnew.htm"><img src="../gifs/whatsnew.gif" alt="WHAT'S NEW | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=5 width=56 height=54></a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a><a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="feedback.gif" alt="Feedback | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46></a><a href="subscrib.htm"><img src="../gifs/subscrib.gif" alt="Subscribe" align=bottom border=0 width=90 height=46></a> </p>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<p><i>Z</i> is a monthly magazine featuring analysis, commentary, and humor on politics, economics, culture, foreign policy, and 
day-to-day life. </p>
<dl>
<dt><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/about.gif" alt="[About Z Magazine]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=10 width=92 height=22></a><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/zmag0cap.gif" align=bottom border=0 hspace=8 vspace=3 width=108 height=37></a></dt>
<dd>A summary of <i>Z</i>'s editorial purposes and policies, financing, and submissions policies. </dd>
<dt><a href="contents.htm"><img src="../gifs/contents.gif" alt="[Contents]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=133 height=22></a></dt>
<dd>Tables of contents from some recent issues of <i>Z</i>, with a sampling of articles. </dd>
<dt><a href="http://www.worldmedia.com/cgi-shl/dbml.exe?template=cfo/confer/prefrncs/main.dbm&amp;CID=16"><img src="../gifs/chat.gif" alt="[Chat Center]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=175 height=22></a></dt>
<dd>Here you can access our new public forum for interactively discussing the contents of <i>Z Magazine</i> and other issues. 
We have online forums you can participate in, posting messages and seeing other people's responses. Web forums are 
a bit spotty in use and functionality, but on <a href="../lbbs/index.htm">LOL</a>, a much wider range of <a href="../lbbs/forums/index.htm">electronic discussion groups</a> are available, 
with a far more robust interface and more in-depth treatment of diverse issues featuring such Z participants as Noam 
Chomsky, Michael Albert, and others. </dd>
<dt><a href="contribs.htm"><img src="contribs.gif" alt="[Contributors]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=187 height=22></a></dt>
<dd>Introductions to some of <i>Z</i>'s artists and writers, with links to a sampling of their articles, including Noam Chomsky, 
bell hooks, Edward Herman, Barbara Ehrenreich, and many others. </dd>
<dt><a href="staff.htm"><img src="../gifs/staff.gif" alt="[Staff]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=70 height=24></a></dt>
<dd>Introductions to the folks who put together <i>Z</i> every month. </dd>
<dt><a href="subscrib.htm"><img src="../gifs/subs.gif" alt="[Subscriptions]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=143 height=24></a></dt>
<dd>How to subscribe to <i>Z</i> Magazine. </dd>
</dl>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><font size=2>A Product of The Institute for Social and Cultural Communications. <br>
Updated: 17 June 1996 </font></p>
