<head>
<title>LBBS: The Left On Line Bulletin Board System</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h2 align=center><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/lglbbs.gif" alt="LBBS: The Left On Line Bulletin Board System" align=bottom border=0 width=445 height=54></a></h2>
<hr>
<p align=center><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37></a><a href="whatsnew.htm"><img src="../gifs/whatsnew.gif" alt="WHAT'S NEW | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=5 width=56 height=54></a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a><a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46></a><a href="subscrib.htm"><img src="../gifs/subscrib.gif" alt="Subscribe" align=bottom border=0 width=90 height=46></a> </p>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<p>LOL<b> </b>(also known as LBBS) is a political bulletin board system featuring discussion groups called forums, downloadable 
files, polls, activism modules, online games, calenders, e-mail, and many other resources. </p>
<p>LOL is for sharing information and ideas, developing political agendas, and participating in a continuous town meeting of 
the progressive community. </p>
<p>Besides these exclusive resources, LOL also offers <b>Internet access</b> over your modem via a SLIP connection, complete 
with: </p>
<ul>
<li>Internet email </li>
<li>telnet </li>
<li>Usenet Groups</li>
<li>the World Wide Web (WWW) </li>
<li>and more. </li>
</ul>
<dd><a href="../lolu/index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smlolu.gif" align=bottom border=0 hspace=10 width=144 height=71></a></dd>
<dd><dl>
<dd>LBBS also hosts the <a href="../lolu/index.htm">Left On Line University (LOL)</a>. </dd>
</dl>
</dd>
<dt><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/about.gif" alt="[About LBBS]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=92 height=22></a><a href="about.htm"><img src="../gifs/hlbbs.gif" align=bottom border=0 hspace=8 vspace=6 width=120 height=33></a></dt>
<dl>
<dd>Descriptions of the purposes, finances, and structure of LOL, including links to co-sponsor's home pages. </dd>
<dt><a href="contents.htm"><img src="../gifs/contents.gif" alt="[Contents]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=133 height=22></a></dt>
<dd>Descriptions of LOL's file libraries and electronic poll facilities. </dd>
<dt><a href="forums/index.htm"><img src="../gifs/chat.gif" alt="[Chat]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=175 height=22></a></dt>
<dd>A description, with some samples, of the LBBS electronic ``chat'' forums: </dd>
<dd><dir>
<li>featuring noted Z writers such as Noam Chomsky </li>
<li>about such diverse topics as youth, racism, political humor, sexual politics, foreign policy, economic vision, 
current events, philosophy, movies, music, gender, schooling, etc. </li>
</dir>
</dd>
<dt><a href="internet.htm"><img src="internet.gif" alt="[Internet]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=118 height=22></a></dt>
<dd>An outline of LOL internet connectivity options. </dd>
<dt><a href="staff.htm"><img src="../gifs/staff.gif" alt="[Staff]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=70 height=24></a></dt>
<dd>Introductions to LOL's System Operators. </dd>
<dt><a href="subscrib.htm"><img src="../gifs/subs.gif" alt="[Subscribe]" align=bottom border=0 vspace=3 width=143 height=24></a></dt>
<dd>How to become a member of LOL. </dd>
</dl>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p><font size=2>A Project of The Institute for Social and Cultural Communications. <br>
Updated: 18 June 1996 </font></p>
