<head>
<title>Z Media Institute</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h2><a href="index.htm"><img src="../gifs/titzmi.gif" alt="Z Magazine" align=top border=0 width=121 height=95></a><img src="../gifs/contents.gif" alt=" Contents" align=top hspace=4 width=133 height=22></h2>
<hr>
<p><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37></a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a><a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback |" align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46></a></p>
<hr>
<h1>Welcome to Z Media Institute</h1>
<p>The Z Media Institute is held each year in early June in a delightful ocean front setting in Woods Hole, Massachusetts. The nine day 
sessions provide training in general political education and radical media work. Focuses include political studies, media studies, 
organizational skills and studies, computer skills and techniques. The program involves four course sessions each day plus project 
groups and evening lectures from Noam Chomsky, Bell Hooks, Barbara Ehrenreich, Ron Daniels, Lydia Sargent, and Michael Albert.</p>
<hr>
