<head>
<title>LBBS: Subscriptions</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h1><img src="../gifs/subs-to.gif" alt="Subscribe to " align=absbottom hspace=2 width=185 height=24><a href="index.htm"><img src="../gifs/hlbbs.gif" alt="LBBS" align=bottom border=0 hspace=8 width=120 height=33></a> </h1>
<hr>
<p><a><img src="../gifs/smlbbs.gif" alt="LBBS | " align=middle hspace=4 width=144 height=65> </a><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37> </a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a> <a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback" align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46> </a></p>
<hr>
<h3>Terms</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>Joining LOL involves no sign on fee at all. There are fees for use, however.</p>
<p>It is very important to realize that LOL uses special technology to limit your online time for E-Mail and Forum use. You 
don't have to read, write, or even search while online but can instead do all productive work regarding forums and E-Mail 
unconnected, at no cost. Use of other functions, including web browsing, does require that you be connected, however.</p>
<p>There are two billing options--to become a <strong>Basic Member</strong> or a <strong>Sustaining Member</strong>.</p>
<dl>
<dt>Members pay $10 a month and get unlimited telnet (or browser) access (if you have another internet account to telnet or 
browse to us from), unlimited long distance access, or two free hours of local call access via numbers all over the country 
(UUNET is our provider). If you are a Basic Member and connect via local calls and use your two free hours in any given 
month, each additional hour is $1.50 (but should drop to $1 an hour within months).</dt>
<dt>&nbsp;</dt>
<dt>Sustaining Members pay $15 a month. They also get unlimited telnet (or browser) access and unlimited long distance 
access. But Sustaining Members get 8 free hours of local call connection each month with the save rates for each additional 
hour as Members pay. Additionally, in major urban areas we are adding installations that will allow Sustaining Members to 
get unlimited local call access for their $15 per month fee.</dt>
</dl>
</blockquote>
<h3>Subscribe by phone</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>Call us at <strong>(508) 548-9063</strong>. Be ready to tell us </p>
<ul>
<li>your name and the address to which <br>
you would like the materials mailed </li>
<li>your credit card number (Visa or Mastercard) <br>
and expiration date </li>
<li>a user ID (public) and a password (private!) <br>
that you wish to have </li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<h3>Subscribe by email or by electronic form</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>If you wish, you can send us <strong>email with your credit card number and experation date, your return address, your 
software operating system, the user id you would like, and the password you would like </strong>but you do this at your own 
risk as we haven't as yet incorporated the capability to accept secure connections.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>A Product of The Institute for Social and Cultural Communications. <br>
Updated: 17 June 1996</p>
</body>

</html>
</DOC>
