<html>

<head>
<title>LBBS: Contents</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h1><img src="../gifs/hlbbs.gif" alt="LBBS" align=bottom hspace=8 width=120 height=33><img src="../gifs/contents.gif" alt=" Contents" align=absbottom hspace=2 width=133 height=22></h1>
<hr>
<p><a><img src="../gifs/smlbbs.gif" alt="LBBS | " align=bottom hspace=4 width=144 height=65></a><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37></a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a><a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback" align=bottom border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46></a></p>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<p>Left on Line is a comprehensive online system in much the same manner as American On Line or other such systems. It 
exists, however, as one part of the ShareWorld Community of online systems. As a result LOL users not only get LOL 
offerings, and full Internet Connectivity, but also a variety of offerings from other OnLine systems in the ShareWorld 
community such as Nation On Line, Wilderness On Line, Greenpeace On Line, etc.</p>
<h3>Basic Left On Line (LOL) Functionality</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="forums/index.htm">LOL Forums</a>: a rich set of discussion areas with offline reading/writing, etc.</li>
<li><a href="internet.htm">LOL Internet Connectivity</a>: Full internet connectivity including web browsing, usenet groups, irc, etc. etc.</li>
<li>LOL Guide to the Internet to help new users navigate with browsers, etc.</li>
<li>E-Mail with offline use, message formating, spell checking, filing, etc.</li>
<li>File Libraries including archives of articles by diverse individuals plus contributions from other co-sponsoring 
organizations and extensive shareware</li>
<li>Activism on Line by email and fax</li>
<li>Poll facilities allow voting by the LOL community, including instant online statistical summaries of poll answers. </li>
<li>Entertainment center includes online games like chess and checkers, etc.</li>
<li>Facilities for meeting people online</li>
<li>Easy Installation</li>
<li>A congenial, civil environment, without harassment, flaming, etc.</li>
<li>Friendly tech support</li>
<li>Mostly 28.8 lines, also telnet access -- low rates</li>
<li>Teleconferencing with audio on the way</li>
<li>and much more...</li>
</ul>
<h3>Related ShareWorld Functionality</h3>
<ul>
<li>Online course offerings</li>
<li>Online radio offerings</li>
<li>Job offerings system on line</li>
<li>Forum access across the ShareWorld community of online systems</li>
<li>Book and magazine clubs on line</li>
<li>Socializing On Line</li>
<li>Chldren's Center and Children's Guide to the Internet</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>Updated: 17 June 1996</p>
</body>

</html>
