<html>

<head>
<title>LOLU: About</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h1><img src="../gifs/about.gif" alt="About " align=absbottom width=92 height=22> <a href="index.htm"><img src="../gifs/hlolu.gif" alt="LOLU" align=bottom border=0 hspace=8 width=96 height=28></a> </h1>
<hr>
<p><a><img src="../gifs/smlolu.gif" alt="LOLU | " align=middle hspace=4 width=144 height=71> </a><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37> </a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a> <a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback" align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46> </a></p>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<h3>Purpose</h3>
<p>Left On Line University aims to provide high quality courses across a range of disciplines and topics, inexpensively, and 
via telecommunications. In this way it provides access to quality faculty and classmates to people from all over the world. 
LOLU simultaneously raises consciousness and creates new ties among people who share the LOLU experience. </p>
<h3>Structure</h3>
<p>Each course runs for 10-15 weeks, the duration of each LOLU semester. Lecture courses involve weekly lectures posted by 
the faculty, and week-long discussions of the contents and derivative issues. Reading courses function similarly, but with 
reading assignments rather than lectures as the basis of discussion. </p>
<p>Decisions as to what course shall be given rest ultimate with the LOLU staff. But the procedure for organizing and offering 
a course is to petition any LBBS co-sponsor to sponsor the course, in which case, other than for redundancy, the course will 
appear in the LOLU catalog. </p>
<h3>Finances</h3>
<p>The current fees for course are $75 to take a course, and $30 to audit. There are special considerations given to those who 
truly cannot afford the going rates, though, since these fees are already very low, only the most extreme circumstances lead 
to further reductions. </p>
<p>The revenues of LOLU are divided, 50% to the faculty and 50% to the University Project. The faculty divide up their share 
of the income partially proportionately to the size of their classes, partially on a one course one share basis. </p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>A project of The Institute for Social and Cultural Communications. <br>
Updated: 18 June 1996</p>
</body>

</html>
