<html>

<head>
<title>LOLU: SUBHEAD</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFA" link="#CC0000" vlink="#000055" alink="#FF3300">
<h1><img src="../gifs/subs-to.gif" alt="Subscribe to " align=absbottom hspace=8 width=185 height=24> <a href="index.htm"><img src="../gifs/hlolu.gif" alt="LOLU" align=bottom border=0 width=96 height=28></a> </h1>
<hr>
<p><a href="index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smlolu.gif" alt="LOLU | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=144 height=71></a><a> </a><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=73 height=37> </a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=56 height=54></a> <a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback" align=middle border=0 hspace=4 width=90 height=46> </a></p>
<hr>
<blockquote>
<h3>LOLU Registration Terms</h3>
<p>LOLU semesters begin February 1, June 1, and October 1, and run for 10 weeks. Numerous courses are given each semester 
and any LBBS member can register to take or audit any number of LOLU courses. </p>
<p>Courses are of two types: seminar and lecture. In the former there are generally weekly readings, followed by discussions 
led by the faculty person in charge. In the lecture courses there may be readings, but there will be weekly lectures, with 
subsequent discussion, question and answer, etc. Some courses include writing assignment, some do not. </p>
<p>It is possible to audit a course ($30) or to take a course ($75). In the former case you can only read all the available 
material. In the latter case, you can also participate, asking questions, writing comments, engaging in discussion, doing 
writing assignments, etc., online. </p>
<h3>College Credit for a LOLU Courses</h3>
<p>LOLU courses are very serious endeavors often superceding (should you choose the option of full participation and 
involvement) in information and time commitment many university courses. </p>
<p>However, LOLU courses do not automatically carry university credit. Whether we could arrange some sort of link with 
some school to provide this or not is unclear, but that it would increase the cost of the classes manyfold (due to the fee we 
would have to pay the university) is a fact. Typical online university level college credit courses are in the $1,500-$2,500 
price range. </p>
<p>We have felt, therefore, that it made more sense for students wanting credits to sign up for a reading course or independent 
study with some empathetic faculty person who was willing to have LOLU course participation as the course content. This 
way, we keep our fees down, and students who really want credits for the involvement can find it. </p>
<h3>To register for a LOLU Course</h3>
<p>To take a LOLU course you must be a member of LBBS. Once you are, you can register for a LOLU course by Email, or, if 
you prefer, by slow mail. The course catalog is always available online, and registration requires only sending a message 
with relevant credit card information and course designations included. </p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>A Product of The Institute for Social and Cultural Communications. <br>
Updated: 17 October 1995 </p>
</body>

</html>
