<HR>
<H1><IMG SRC="../gifs/titzmi.gif" ALT="Z Magazine" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0">
Information</H1>
<HR>
<H2>
Purposes and Policies</H2>
<P>Z Media Institute exists to share knowledge, skills, and information
relevant to working effectively with media in the United States. The program
emphasizes the short comings of mainstream media and the possibilities of
alternative media. </P>
<P>ZMI incorporates courses in political theory, media studies, organizational
skills, and technical skills, with project groups in radio, print, and
organizing work.</P>
<P>The goal of ZMI is to help progressive people initiate or work more
effectively within alternative media or activist institutions, and to better
media and its uses.</P>
<HR>
<H2>Financing and Budget</H2>
<P>ZMI's costs (estimated here for the June 1995 session) are room and board
for all attendees and faculty ($47,000), staff and lecturer's fees and travel
expenses ($7,500), computer rentals, text production, and general miscellaneous
costs ($3,500), for a total of $58,000.</P>
<P>ZMI's revenues are the fees paid by students. The full price is $1,000.
Scholarships range from $250 to $750. We are still arranging fees and
acceptances for June 1995, but the goal is to schedule income of about $60,000
for the 80 attending students. </P>
<P>There is, regrettably, no outside funding support for ZMI. On the other hand
much of the staff and faculty time is donated.</P>
<P>Anyone who wishes to help ZMI by providing funds that will enable an
expansion of scholarships, can do so by making a tax deductible donation. Call
508-548-9063 for more information.</P>
<HR>       
</BODY>
</HTML>
