<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "+//ISBN 82-7640-037::WWW//DTD HTML//EN//2.0" "html.dtd">
<p><a href="../index.htm"><img src="../gifs/smznet.gif" alt="ZNet | " hspace=4 border=0 height=37 width=73 align=center></a><a href="../help.htm"><img src="../gifs/help.gif" alt="HELP | " hspace=4 border=0 height=54 width=56 align=center></a><a href="mailto:sysop@lbbs.org"><img src="../gifs/feedback.gif" alt="Feedback |" hspace=4 border=0 height=46 width=90 align=center></a></p>

<h1><img src="../gifs/titzmi.gif" alt="Z Magazine" border=0 height=95 width=121 align=top>Logistics</h1>

<p>
<hr></p>

<h2>Where</h2>

<p>ZMI is held in Wood Hole Massachusetts. Students are housed at a local
Inn where we rent sufficient rooms. Classes are held at a number of nearby
sites. Dining is at the Swope Dining Hall, which is part of the Marine
Biology Laboratories. The site is on the water, small town living. Natural,
serene, a good balance for the hectic pace of the program.</p>

<h2>When</h2>

<p>ZMI is held yearly in June. In 1996 the session will run from June 5
to June 14.</p>

<p>
<hr></p>

<h2>Fees</h2>

<p>The full fee for ZMI is $1,000 to cover room, board, classes, computers,
etc. Scholarships range from $250 to $500 but are in short supply. The
first payment each year is due March 1, to help us reserve housing. All
payments must be made by the sessions opening.</p>

<p>
<hr></p>

</body>
