    <p align="left"><font size="2">The above icons take you to
    various component systems within the ZNet Web Site. It is
    also possible, however, to use our </font><a
    href="tableof.htm"><font size="2">Table of Contents Page</font></a><font
    size="2">, which lists all the pages in our site, or our
    summary </font><a href="about.html"><font size="2">About ZNet</font></a><font
    size="2"> page, or our search engine if you have particular
    interests you want to pursue. For example, you might want to
    see a list of pages within the site that mention human
    nature, or Clinton, or socialism and not capitalism, or Iraq
    or Turkey, etc. You can find a list of pages, and go to any
    one, using the following handy, and quick, search engine. The
    found pages will be listed below. Just type in the key word
    or phrase or instruction and then click Start Search. To
    search again, just type in a new word and click Start Search,
    again.</font></p>
    <p align="left"><font size="2">You can use and, or
    combinations. So you might type in &quot;Chomsky and
    Clinton,&quot; or &quot;human and nature or biology,&quot; or
    Iran, or &quot;Iran or Gulf,&quot; and so on. You can also
    you an asterisk at the end of a key, so, for exampe, you
    could type in social* or cap* and so on.</font></p>
