<h1>Forum Messages from Markets Forum in LBBS</h1>

<hr>

<blockquote>
    <p>Markets is another busy LOL forum. It's focus is a
    discussion of the virtues and debits of markets. However,
    unlike most intellectual exchanges in the U.S. and the world
    today, here there is a very strong representation by people
    who feel the the debits of markets are so great that the only
    way to attain a desirable economy is to replace markets with
    some other superior mode of allocation.</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
    <p>A companion forum in the LBBS system discusses reforms to
    markets, and the LOL forum Parecon, which is also excerpted
    in this Web Site, discusses an alternative economic vision. A
    very active participant in the market forum is Robin Hahnel,
    an economist from American University. He is the RH&gt; in
    the posts we link to below, again culled from messages posted
    in early April.</p>
</blockquote>

