<P><CITE>
The following is a message posted to the Movies Forum, continuing responding to
a new thread of discussion.</CITE></P>
<HR>
<H1>On Gump-ism
</H1>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>IM&gt; says: I just saw Forrest Gump and really disliked it.
Everyone I've talked to thought it was great. Does anyone else hate it? Also,
I'm a little too young to remember the '60s very well. Is that what they were
really like?</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I thought Gump was the purest horseshit I have tasted in some time. For
those who have trashed Pulp Fiction in this forum, if you seek a really debased,
dishonest and disgusting film, look no farther.</P>
<P>As to whether this film depicts the 60s accurately, no. Unfortunately, like
most Hollywood revisionist history, it contains enough of a ring of truth to
seem convincing, even to those who were there and should know better. For
example, if I recall correctly, the only really bad character in the film was
the 60s radical. He spouted slogans, manipulated remorselessly, and abused
Gump's girlfriend, who wimpishly went back to him. Did we know characters like
him? Yes. Was sexism a problem in many 60s movements? Yes. (But feminism has
become perhaps the most successful of the 60s movements.) So is this guy
representative of 60s activists? Bullshit. (Though he certainly reminds me of
Newt.) One could go on with other examples. The movie was trash, part of the
broad assault by the cultural managers on the legacy of a time when decency,
equality, participation, solidarity, sex and fun tried to make their mark on our
culture.</P>
<P>For better views on the 60s, there was a good discussion on LBBS a while
ago, I think in popcult, that contained a number of reminiscenses.  Also, Howard
Zinn's articles in recent Z mags provide a wonderful flavor of the early 60s.
</P>
<P>I do hope LOLU can get a course going on that period--and others.  Surveys
are fine, but many of us would like something sharper and deeper. I also wonder
if anyone is aware of what they consider to be good histories of the 60s.</P> 
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
