<H1>Forum Messages from the Participatory Economics Forum in LBBS</H1>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>The ParEcon forum in LBBS discusses economic vision and
particularly the vision named Participatory Economics put forward in a number of
volumes by Michael Albert and Robin Hahnel.The forum is exceptionally busy, with
commentary mostly about how to organize work, consumption, allocation, and
ownership in the large, but also including some more specific and narrow
exchanges about details of the participatory economic vision, and economic
vision more generally,  including, for example, schooling in relation to the
economy, insurance in a good economy, law suits, etc.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>The excerpts here are all from the first few days of April.
They focus mostly on the idea of balanced job complexes, on the one hand, and
issues of insurance and law, on the other, two active threads right now...  
