<H1>Forum Messages from the Participatory Economics Forum in LBBS</H1>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>The Schools forum in LBBS discusses all manner of issues
related to public schools and pre-college education. A very active exchange was
under way, including students, parents, teachers, and even a school founder in
early April when these messages were culled, regarding the efficacy of dropping
out as an educational strategy, and, in context of this, the character of public
schools.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
