<HR>
<H1>Heather Replies re High School</H1>
<P>I disagree with you. I do not recomnend dropping out of high school. It is
true that high schools feed us a lot of bullshit. But we're going to be exposed
to that bullshit even if we drop out. Just turn on the TV and watch the news.
The world is unfair, but it is the world we live in and we have to deal with it.
Dropping out of high school is not a good way to fight the system. Dropping out
of high school just makes you more powerless so it is harder to fight the
system. We all have to eat, and trying to survive in this world without a high
school diploma is damned near impossible unless you get involved with drug
dealing or some other sort of criminal operation (which I do not advise because
crime hurts everyone, especially the poor and powerless). Even if you do manage
to survive without a high school diploma, surviving will be so hard and take up
so much of your time that you won't have the time to fight for any of your
causes. Also, education does help you prepare for many things in life. This is a
classist society and uneducated people are immediately scoffed at and discarded
when they speak up no matter how much worth their ideas might have. However, if
that same idea is stated by an educated person, it is more likely to be given a
moment's thought. Yeah, it's unfair, but it is the way the world works. Just
refusing to deal with the world because it's unfair won't change its unfairness,
it'll just make you a hermit (possibly a starving hermit).</P>
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
