<title>It's Still A Dick Thing </title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#F8F8F8" link="#001F76" vlink="#001F76"
alink="#001F76">

<blockquote>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <blockquote>
        <h2>from the pages of<img src="../oldsmzma.gif" alt="../"
        align="top" hspace="4" width="108" height="37"> </h2>
    </blockquote>
    <hr>
    <h1 align="center">It's Still A Dick Thing </h1>
    <p align="center"><font size="4"><em>Lydia Sargent </em></font></p>
    <p align="center"><font size="4"><em></em></font>&nbsp;</p>
    <blockquote>
        <p>Four years ago (&quot;It's a Dick Thing,&quot; Sept.
        90), Hotel Satire advised you gals to stay inside for the
        duration of the summer. Why? Cause summer, we asserted,
        is the season of the dicks. We were roused to this
        assertion by Spike Lee's then new film, Mo' Better Blues,
        where the &quot;hero&quot; is &quot;seeing&quot; two
        women. When confronted by one of them (who is angry,
        therefore hysterical) as to why he is such a
        &quot;dog&quot; as to do this, he replies, &quot;It's a
        dick thing.&quot; She barks back (annoyed, therefore a
        bitch), &quot;A dick thing!?&quot; He repeats calmly and
        firmly, &quot;A dick thing.&quot; </p>
        <p>While shocked by the language, we realized at the time
        that it applied to the entire summer season. Well, gals,
        we must advise you again in this matter. Why? Because
        Summer 1994 looks dickier than usual, with the O.J. thing
        and the World Cup Soccer thing and the Threat of Invasion
        thing. Check it out. The World Cup thing is a dick thing.
        There are few women to be found other than in the stands
        and in the audience, passively watching and applauding
        (therefore attractive), as opposed to playing/competing
        (unattractive). Check the sports page's weekly scores of
        various professional, minor, and park leagues. They have
        a regular of Michael Jordan's statistics in minor league
        baseball--he's batting .197. This is clearly more
        important than covering any sport played by any gal at
        any time. That's because (a) gals aren't good at sports
        and, unlike Michael Jordan, should not be allowed to do
        what they aren't good at; and (b) gals playing sports are
        either lesbians (therefore not gals) or sexy (therefore
        not athletes). </p>
        <p>Check it out. The O.J. thing is a dick thing. First,
        it prepares guys for the upcoming football season when
        they can cut those dicks loose. Second, it's a profit
        making thing which is, and always will be, gals, a dick
        thing. O.J. Trading Cards are selling briskly, and O.J.
        watches are hitting the market as we speak. I know many
        of you femcomlesgals are harping on the women and
        battering/wife murdering aspect of the O.J. thing. That's
        because you do not understand the nature of
        markets/greed/dicks which have always benefited from
        general mayhem. Plus, if that gal, Nicole, had stayed
        inside (and celibate), dutifully packing lunches and
        watching O.J. on TV sports events, instead of divorcing
        and dating, she'd be alive today. Plus as we know, the
        real harassers and batterers are gals (ignore the
        statistics, please). How do we know? Because,
        appropriately, Hollywood will soon deal with the issue of
        battering by making a movie based on Michael Crichton's
        book about a female harasser. Also, because gals'
        interference in dickosterone summer activities is
        tantamount to harassment. </p>
        <p>Clearly, Gals, you need to review the protocol we set
        forward in 1990. So here goes. Gals. Listen up. Summer is
        not your thing. Go inside for the duration. Do not emerge
        except to shop or sunbathe or chauffeur men and/or little
        children to places where they can have fun. Many of you
        have tried to play ball or go boating. Stop it. Guys do
        not want you bouncing your breasts out there on the ball
        field or grabbing rudders on the high seas. Don't
        question it. It's a dick thing. </p>
        <p>Gals. If there's a motor involved, if there's
        horsepower and RPM's in the vicinity, we're talking
        dicks. Never interfere with dicks and their throbbing
        engines. You can sit next to him (cars) and provide food
        and read the map (if capable). You can snuggle behind him
        (motorcycles) while he straddles maximum horse power. You
        can pack a lunch and pose (boats) while he captains and
        comes about, advanced dick concepts beyond a gal's
        comprehension. You may ride a bikes (no motors involved),
        but only to lose weight or to seek out the shopping
        possibilities. Be sure to pose prettily next to the bike
        as often as you actually ride the thing. Try to ride the
        rusty old 3-speed you had when you were 12 years old. No
        advanced concepts for you, like 21 gears. Also. Never go
        off the trail, onto dirt. Instead, lag behind looking at
        pretty flowers or checking out future shopping
        possibilities. </p>
        <p>Stay away from the golf course. Or any activity
        involving a club and a small white ball. It's a dick
        thing. And there will be no competing with guys. At
        anything. Badminton. Parcheesi. Miniature golf. Croquet.
        If he does talk you into playing a game with him, there
        will be no beating of the dicks. Most gals learn this at
        birth. Winning is a dick thing. Nuff said. </p>
        <p>What can gals do during the summer? Gals can pack a
        picnic, sit on a grassy knoll, a sand dune, or a boat
        deck, tending to the sandwiches and large quantities of
        small children while watching their dick steer, run,
        ride, straddle, kick, and chase balls. Keep the thermos
        o' beer and the cold chicken at the ready. Gals can also
        engage in lite tennis and other lite sports like walking
        with other gal friends, discussing hair care products or
        their guys' cholesterol level. </p>
        <p>Gals can shop--either at quaint tourist traps, malls,
        or fashion outlets. If you bring your dick to the mall
        (on a rainy day), let him sit in the car close to his
        motor while you shop. Then take him to see the summer's
        latest crop of dick movies. Summer 94 really delivers in
        this department. What with The Shadow, The Gump, The
        Blown Away, The Schwarzenegger, The Wolf, The Earp,
        there's nary a gal to be seen except as the usual
        wives/prostitutes (in Earp they're interchangeable). Or
        in remakes of 1930s movies (Julia Roberts in I Love
        Trouble)in which gals got to have actual jobs and
        dialogue before they married and disappeared from the
        face of the earth. This summer, in Baby's Day Out,even a
        boy baby (who can barely walk and can't talk gets a
        bigger role than any Hollywood gal has had in the last
        decade. </p>
        <p>Now many of you gals keep losing touch with your guys
        dicks, so to speak. You write constantly and ask &quot;Is
        that all, Hotel Satire gal? We feed their dicks and
        discuss fingernail lengths? Can't we do a little
        something more during those hot summer months?&quot; I
        always write back and ask, &quot;Like what?&quot; </p>
        <p>Well, gals, this summer only, we have a special offer
        to maximize gals' enhancement of the dick! Yes. Thanks to
        Vogue, which has recently been shooting fashion spreads
        in Vietnamese rice paddies and Shanghai dumpling
        restaurants, and thanks also to your local daily
        newspaper, which runs those daily bra ads on page 3 (or
        is it 7?) next to news stories of pain and suffering, we
        are permitting you gals to pose half nude in various
        unusual venues. Just make sure your posing clearly
        supports the notion that gals: (a) have the morals of a
        tsetse fly; (b) are sex objects, decorations, and twits
        no matter what else they may try to do, like be cops or
        nuclear physicists; (c) have no political consciousness
        or comprehension of world events whatsoever. </p>
        <p>Now calm down, Gals. This offer is extraordinary and
        wonderful, I know. I sense that the opportunity to
        humiliate yourselves in this fashion is causing mass
        stampedes around the country. But please, a little taste,
        a little creativity. We refer you to the policewoman,
        Carol Shaya, who posed for Playboy as part of their
        &quot;real people&quot; series. Posing nude while
        &quot;arresting&quot; people on the mean streets of the
        South Bronx is inspiring, to say the least. </p>
        <p>If you are not a policewoman and/or you think sexy
        poses don't go with law and order, we have some other
        tasteful suggestions for gal poses in unusual venues. How
        about posing on O.J.'s Bronco in stretch pants and Ice
        Spice lipstick? Now there's a venue that screams for gal
        decor. Or on the field during a World Cup Soccer game in
        a tank top with the briefest of miniskirts. Or in a face
        cage in Bangkok? Or as a sexy gal with a little girl's
        face (never to early to get provocative) in a story about
        busing/desegregation? Or in future chic in a troop
        deployment to Haiti? Or in silver in Rwanda. </p>
        <p>There's no end to the possibilities. Gals. Don't
        delay. Get into your best lingerie, Joan of Arc ivory
        tulle, appliqu&#142;ed with corset-shaped cutout loosely
        lace at the sides avec Pink Fog lipstick, and decorate
        that story about N. Korea. But hurry. This offer won't
        last long. Then it's back to mixing up the Kool Aid, or
        lying decoratively on a blanket watching the dicks roam
        where they may. </p>
        <p>Yeah. It's still a dick thing. </p>
    </blockquote>
</blockquote>

